      <title>Recess Starts - GovTrack.us</title>
      <link>https://govtrack.us/posts/436/2024-08-02_recess-starts</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://govtrack.us/posts/436/2024-08-02_recess-starts</guid>
      <description>&lt;div id="content"&gt; 				 			   	  				 &lt;h1&gt;Recess Starts&lt;/h1&gt;  &lt;div class="row"&gt;     &lt;div class="col-md order-md-2" style="margin-bottom: 2em"&gt;         &lt;div class="ms-md-3" style="border: 1px solid #777; border-radius: 1em; padding: 1em; background-color: #F9F9F9;"&gt;         &lt;h2&gt;Get Legislative Recap Updates In Your Inbox!&lt;/h2&gt;         &lt;p&gt;Sign up (it&amp;rsquo;s free!) to get posts like this straight to your inbox. You&amp;rsquo;ll be able to choose posts from these categories:&lt;/p&gt;         &lt;p&gt;Legislative Preview &amp;nbsp; &amp;ndash; &amp;nbsp; Legislative Recap &amp;nbsp; &amp;ndash; &amp;nbsp; Analysis and Commentary &amp;nbsp; &amp;ndash; &amp;nbsp; News About GovTrack &amp;nbsp; &amp;ndash; &amp;nbsp; Using GovTrack Tips&lt;/p&gt;         &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://govtrack.us/accounts/lists" class="btn btn-primary"&gt;Sign Up &amp;raquo;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;      &lt;div class="col-md"&gt;        &lt;p&gt;           Aug 2, 2024           &amp;middot; by Amy West       &lt;/p&gt;        &lt;p&gt;Your GovTracker was a little premature about Congress being in recess in last week's recap because the Senate stayed in to do a little work this week.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Now&lt;/em&gt; both chambers are out until Sept. 9.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;So what did the Senate do with their week?&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Nominations&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;p&gt;The Senate &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/votes"&gt;confirmed four judges and an ambassador&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h2&gt;KOSA&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/votes/118-2024/s221"&gt;S. 2073: Kids Online Safety and Privacy Act&lt;/a&gt; is a bill originally known as the "Kids Online Safety Act" which is why the acronym you'll see people using is KOSA. It's a complex bill that has generated both &lt;a href="https://www.nbcnews.com/tech/tech-news/will-kosa-coppa-20-controversial-bills-explained-rcna163243"&gt;bipartisan support and opposition as summarized by NBC&lt;/a&gt;. Despite the level of controversy, it passed the Senate &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/votes/118-2024/s221"&gt;91-3&lt;/a&gt;. Yesterday, numerous reports indicated that the bill will not be brought up in the House. So, despite its big majority in the Senate, it's &lt;a href="https://punchbowl.news/article/senate/schumer-july-biden-out-democrats-hopes-in-senate/"&gt;likely dead for this Congress&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Tax Relief Bill&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Senate procedure note&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;In the Senate, the debate phase for a bill has no defined end. To move to a vote on the bill itself, the Senate has to agree to end debate. &lt;a href="https://www.senate.gov/about/powers-procedures/filibusters-cloture.htm"&gt;This kind of vote is called a "cloture" vote&lt;/a&gt;. It's also what people mean when they talk about the filibuster. To pass - that is, to end debate - 60 Senators have to get on board. With the Senate almost evenly split, few bills can jump this hurdle. And the one below did not.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr7024"&gt;H.R. 7024: Tax Relief for American Families and Workers Act of 2024&lt;/a&gt; would provide tax relief in various forms for both businesses and families. It failed &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/votes/118-2024/s230"&gt;48-44&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;See you next week for a post answering one or maybe more questions we've received from you!&lt;/p&gt;      &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;  &lt;hr&gt;  &lt;p&gt;    Let us know what you think about these updates    by tooting us on &lt;a rel="me" href="https://mastodon.social/@GovTrack" title="Mastodon"&gt;&lt;i class="fab fa-mastodon"&gt;&lt;/i&gt; Mastodon&lt;/a&gt;    or &lt;a href="https://govtrack.us/contact" style="text-decoration: none"&gt;&lt;i class="fas fa-envelope"&gt;&lt;/i&gt; sending us an email&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;    			&lt;/div&gt;</description>
