      <title>Trump's VP pick Sen. J.D. Vance: His most interesting bills in Congress - GovTrack.us</title>
      <link>https://govtrack.us/posts/431/2024-07-17_trumps-vp-pick-sen-jd-vance-his-most-interesting-bills-in-congress</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://govtrack.us/posts/431/2024-07-17_trumps-vp-pick-sen-jd-vance-his-most-interesting-bills-in-congress</guid>
      <description>&lt;div id="content"&gt; 				 			   	  				 &lt;h1&gt;Trump&amp;#39;s VP pick Sen. J.D. Vance: His most interesting bills in Congress&lt;/h1&gt;  &lt;div class="row"&gt;     &lt;div class="col-md order-md-2" style="margin-bottom: 2em"&gt;         &lt;div class="ms-md-3" style="border: 1px solid #777; border-radius: 1em; padding: 1em; background-color: #F9F9F9;"&gt;         &lt;h2&gt;Get Analysis and Commentary Updates In Your Inbox!&lt;/h2&gt;         &lt;p&gt;Sign up (it&amp;rsquo;s free!) to get posts like this straight to your inbox. You&amp;rsquo;ll be able to choose posts from these categories:&lt;/p&gt;         &lt;p&gt;Legislative Preview &amp;nbsp; &amp;ndash; &amp;nbsp; Legislative Recap &amp;nbsp; &amp;ndash; &amp;nbsp; Analysis and Commentary &amp;nbsp; &amp;ndash; &amp;nbsp; News About GovTrack &amp;nbsp; &amp;ndash; &amp;nbsp; Using GovTrack Tips&lt;/p&gt;         &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://govtrack.us/accounts/lists" class="btn btn-primary"&gt;Sign Up &amp;raquo;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;      &lt;div class="col-md"&gt;        &lt;p&gt;           Jul 17, 2024           &amp;middot; by Jesse Rifkin       &lt;/p&gt;        &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/members/jd_james_vance/456876"&gt;Sen. J.D. Vance (R-OH)&lt;/a&gt; has served as &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/browse?sponsor=456876"&gt;lead sponsor for 36 bills&lt;/a&gt; during the year and a half of his freshman session of Congress so far. GovTrack looked through all his bills and found 8 of the most interesting.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;He's joined Democrats in cosponsoring bills to &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/s2233"&gt;ban sales of products with lethal levels of sodium nitrite&lt;/a&gt;, an increasingly common method of suicide, &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/s1790"&gt;claw back bank executives' compensation when banks go under&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/s576"&gt;increasing fines on railroad companies&lt;/a&gt; (more on that one below).&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;However, the legislation he has introduced himself largely touches on hot-button social issues including immigration, affirmative action and race, transgender issues, and trade with China. He has also proposed &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/s3514"&gt;increasing taxes on major universities&lt;/a&gt; and having &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/s2403"&gt;the federal government backstop community and small regional banks&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Just one of his 36 bills has received a committee vote in Congress, with none yet enacted into law, which is expected for his short tenure.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Regardless, they reveal how Republican presidential nominee Donald Trump's running mate could help govern from the White House.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h4&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/s4045"&gt;East Palestine Health Impact Monitoring Act&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/s576"&gt;Railway Safety Act&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt; &lt;p&gt;The East Palestine Health Impact Monitoring Act would commission a study on the health impacts of February 2023's Norfolk Southern train derailment and toxic chemical spill in East Palestine, Ohio.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;It's Vance's only bill that has had any action so far, passed by committee 19-2 earlier this year &lt;a href="https://www.youtube.com/live/Y1QoqGwqvCA?si=CZSJvzKaAQ3WyQQQ&amp;amp;t=2973"&gt;despite opposition only from Republicans&lt;/a&gt;: Sens. &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/members/mike_braun/412839"&gt;Mike Braun (R-IN)&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/members/rand_paul/412492"&gt;Rand Paul (R-KY)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The 102-page Railway Safety Act, introduced by &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/members/sherrod_brown/400050"&gt;Sen. Sherrod Brown (D-OH)&lt;/a&gt; with Vance as an original cosponsor, would change a number of railroad regulations in response to the train derailment.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The new rules would include increased fines on railroads, so much so that the Congressional Budget Office says the bill &lt;a href="https://www.cbo.gov/system/files/2024-02/s576.pdf"&gt;would lower the deficit&lt;/a&gt;. Another requirement would mandate that all trains operate with at least two-person crews.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"We owe every American the peace of mind that their community is protected from a catastrophe of this kind," &lt;a href="https://www.vance.senate.gov/press-releases/senators-vance-brown-to-introduce-bipartisan-legislation-to-prevent-train-derailment-disasters/"&gt;Sen. Vance said in a press release&lt;/a&gt;.Â  "One day, the TV cameras will leave and the news cycle will move on, but the needs of those Ohioans will remain."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Railroad industry opponents counter that many components of the bill are solutions in search of a problem. We oppose "provisions including those that mandate crew staffing models, expand hazmat transportation operating requirements, micromanage detector networks, and unnecessarily broaden manual inspections," &lt;a href="https://www.aar.org/news/aar-statement-on-senate-commerce-rail-safety-act-vote/"&gt;the Association of American Railroads (AAR) wrote in a statement&lt;/a&gt;. "In . . . safety legislation, each provision should be clearly designed to rectify a current safety challenge. As reported out of the committee, this bill falls short of that goal."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The Senate Banking, Housing, and Urban Affairs Committee approved the bill in May 2023 &lt;a href="https://www.commerce.senate.gov/2023/5/bipartisan-railway-safety-act-heads-to-senate-floor"&gt;by a 16-11 vote&lt;/a&gt; with most Republicans opposing. It has yet to receive a vote in the full chamber.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;However, some of its provisions have taken effect through other means. In April 2024, the Federal Railroad Administration (FRA) &lt;a href="https://www.transportation.gov/briefing-room/biden-harris-administration-announces-final-rule-train-crew-size-safety-requirements"&gt;mandated minimum two-person crews for freight rail&lt;/a&gt;. In May, Norfolk Southern &lt;a href="https://rollcall.com/2024/05/23/norfolk-southern-agrees-to-1b-in-settlements-for-east-palestine/"&gt;agreed to pay approximately $1 billion to settle lawsuits&lt;/a&gt; brought by a combination of the Justice Department and private citizens.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h4&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/s1109"&gt;English Language Unity Act&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt; &lt;p&gt;While English is by far the most commonly spoken and written language in the U.S., &lt;a href="https://www.usa.gov/official-language-of-us#:%7E:text=Does%20the%20U.S.%20have%20an,it%20as%20their%20official%20language."&gt;there's no official national language&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Many individual states declare English as the official language, though. Not just red states; blue state examples include &lt;a href="https://repository.uclawsf.edu/ca_ballot_props/968/"&gt;California&lt;/a&gt;. Vance's home state of Ohio &lt;a href="https://proenglish.org/ohio/"&gt;doesn't appear to have an official language&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Vance's bill would make English the official national language, a symbolic change, and would require that official functions like laws and proceedings be in English in the 50 states and the District of Columbia. (All laws and virtually all proceedings already are in English there, of course, and Vance's bill does not include Puerto Rico where the government operates primarily in Spanish.)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;It would also &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/s1109/text/is#link=3_a_%7EQ1_6_164_a&amp;amp;nearest=H2436BDEF34324CB2B22EF304D243B74E"&gt;require English proficiency to become a U.S. citizen&lt;/a&gt; -- even though that's &lt;a href="https://www.uscis.gov/policy-manual/volume-12-part-e-chapter-2#:%7E:text=A.%20Educational%20Requirements&amp;amp;text=The%20naturalization%20test%20consists%20of,determined%20by%20a%20civics%20test"&gt;already required&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"This commonsense legislation recognizes an inherent truth: English is the language of this country," &lt;a href="https://www.vance.senate.gov/press-releases/senator-vance-to-introduce-legislation-to-establish-english-as-the-official-language-of-the-united-states/"&gt;Sen. Vance said in a press release&lt;/a&gt;. "The English language has been a cornerstone of American culture for over 250 years. It is far past time for Congress to codify its place into law."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The United Statesâs âmelting potâ metaphor doesnât come from nowhere, however. Native Americans, many colonial settlers, people brought into the country as slaves, people in Spanish territories acquired by the United States in the 1800s, and immigrants throughout that time all have spoken languages other than English.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Opponents counter that such a law sends the wrong message in a country where &lt;a href="https://www.census.gov/library/stories/2022/12/languages-we-speak-in-united-states.html"&gt;67.8 million Americans now speak a language other than English at home&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;President Barack Obama, answering a question on the subject at a Georgia voter forum back in 2008, &lt;a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2008/07/11/us/politics/11checkpoint.html"&gt;said&lt;/a&gt;: "I agree that immigrants should learn English" but argued that an actual law was unnecessary.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Instead of worrying about whether immigrants can learn English â they'll learn English â you need to make sure your child can speak Spanish," Obama said. "You should be thinking about how can your child become bilingual. We should have every child speaking more than one language."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Vance's bill has attracted &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/s1109/cosponsors"&gt;two Republican cosponsors&lt;/a&gt;, Sens. &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/members/kevin_cramer/412555"&gt;Kevin Cramer (R-ND)&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/members/roger_marshall/412704"&gt;Roger Marshall (R-KS)&lt;/a&gt;. The &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr997"&gt;House version&lt;/a&gt; introduced by &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/members/robert_good/456853"&gt;Rep. Bob Good (R-VA5)&lt;/a&gt; has attracted &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr997/cosponsors"&gt;17 Republican cosponsors&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h4&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/s4516"&gt;Dismantle DEI Act&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt; &lt;p&gt;DEI ("Diversity Equity and Inclusion")Â  refers to initiatives to increase representation of historically under-represented and marginalized demographic groups at institutions such as workplaces and in education.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Vance's bill would discontinue all DEI programs across the federal government, plus for private companies that contract with the federal government.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"The DEI agenda is a destructive ideology that breeds hatred and racial division. It has no place in our federal government or anywhere else in our society," &lt;a href="https://www.vance.senate.gov/press-releases/senator-vance-rep-cloud-introduce-legislation-to-eliminate-all-dei-programs-from-the-federal-government/"&gt;Sen. Vance said in a press release&lt;/a&gt;. "Americans' tax dollars should not be co-opted to spread this radical and divisive ideology -- this bill would ensure they are not."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Opponents counter that the federal government has a responsibility to remedy past discrimination and prejudices.Â &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Because advancing equity requires a systematic approach to embedding fairness in decision-making processes, executive departments and agencies must recognize and work to redress inequities in their policies and programs that serve as barriers to equal opportunity," &lt;a href="https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefing-room/presidential-actions/2021/01/20/executive-order-advancing-racial-equity-and-support-for-underserved-communities-through-the-federal-government/"&gt;President Joe Biden wrote in a 2021 executive order on his first day in office&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Vance's bill has attracted &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/s4516/cosponsors"&gt;13 Republican cosponsors&lt;/a&gt;. The &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr8706"&gt;House version&lt;/a&gt; introduced by &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/members/michael_cloud/412746"&gt;Rep. Michael Cloud (R-TX27)&lt;/a&gt; has attracted &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr8706/cosponsors"&gt;61 Republican cosponsors&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h4&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/s2357"&gt;Protect Children's Innocence Act&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Gender-affirming" surgeries, such as breast removal or genital reconstruction, have been performed much more in recent years, with about &lt;a href="https://jamanetwork.com/journals/jamanetworkopen/fullarticle/2808707"&gt;1,000 surgeries performed nationwide per year on patients aged 18 or younger&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Republican policies have zeroed in on minors: &lt;a href="https://www.kff.org/other/dashboard/gender-affirming-care-policy-tracker/"&gt;25 states&lt;/a&gt; have either banned or significantly restricted transgender medical care for minors, including surgeries, hormone treatments, and puberty blockers. All 25 similar state laws were enacted just since 2021, when Arkansas became the first.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Vance's home state of Ohio is among them. In 2023, Gov. Mike DeWine (R) broke with his own party by &lt;a href="https://apnews.com/article/transgender-health-ohio-minors-veto-c615cafed4fc81d32010d47d8853efaf"&gt;vetoing the Enact Ohio Saving Adolescents From Experimentation (SAFE) Act, &lt;/a&gt;which would have banned transgender medical care for minors. But in January 2024, the legislature overrode the veto: &lt;a href="https://www.legislature.ohio.gov/legislation/135/hb68/votes"&gt;65-28 in the state House and 24-8 in the state Senate&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Vance's bill would ban "gender-affirming" medical care for transgender minors nationwide.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The practice would still be permitted for adults. While some states have placed restrictions, no state has outright banned gender-affirming medical care for transgender adults -- though individual &lt;a href="https://www.axios.com/2023/03/29/transgender-health-care-adult-ban-bills"&gt;state legislators in Kansas, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas&lt;/a&gt; have introduced bills to do so.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Under no circumstances should doctors be allowed to perform these gruesome, irreversible operations on underage children," &lt;a href="https://www.vance.senate.gov/press-releases/senator-vance-introduces-legislation-to-ban-gender-reassignment-procedures-on-minors/"&gt;Sen. Vance said in a press release&lt;/a&gt;. "With this legislation, we have an opportunity to save countless young Americans from a lifetime of suffering and regret."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;But studies show &lt;a href="https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/what-the-science-on-gender-affirming-care-for-transgender-kids-really-shows/"&gt;Vance's dire claims aren't actually true&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Opponents of the bill include some conservatives -- including the aforementioned Gov. DeWine, who defended his veto as consistent with pro-life positions on other issues like abortion.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Ultimately, I believe this is about protecting human life. Many parents have told me that their child would be dead today if they had not received the treatment they received from an Ohio children's hospital," &lt;a href="https://content.govdelivery.com/attachments/OHIOGOVERNOR/2023/12/29/file_attachments/2731770/Signed%20Veto%20Message%20HB%2068.pdf"&gt;Gov. DeWine wrote in his veto message&lt;/a&gt;. "I have also been told, by those that are now grown adults, that but for this care, they would have taken their lives when they were teenagers."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Vance's bill has attracted &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/s2357/cosponsors"&gt;two Republican cosponsors&lt;/a&gt;, Sens. &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/members/mike_braun/412839"&gt;Mike Braun (R-IN)&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/members/tommy_tuberville/456796"&gt;Tommy Tuberville (R-AL)&lt;/a&gt;.Â  The &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr5636"&gt;House version&lt;/a&gt; introduced by &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/members/marjorie_greene/456814"&gt;Rep. Marjorie Taylor Greene (R-GA14)&lt;/a&gt; has attracted &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr5636"&gt;47 Republican cosponsors&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h4&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/s2656"&gt;Timely Departure Act&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt; &lt;p&gt;In fiscal year 2022, &lt;a href="https://www.dhs.gov/publication/entryexit-overstay-report"&gt;the most recent data available&lt;/a&gt;, 853,955 foreign travelers overstayed their temporary U.S. visas, or &lt;a href="https://www.dhs.gov/sites/default/files/2023-07/23_0707_FY22_FY23_CBP_Integrated_Entry_Exit_Overstay_Report.pdf#page=6"&gt;3.7% of travelers whose visas expired that year&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Vance's bill would create a new bond system, requiring visa holders to deposit between $5,000 and $15,000 upon entering the U.S., which they'd receive back from the government if they leave by their visa's listed deadline.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"America is a welcoming nation, but we are also a nation of laws," &lt;a href="https://www.vance.senate.gov/press-releases/senator-vance-introduces-legislation-to-crack-down-on-illegal-visa-overstays/"&gt;Sen. Vance said in a press release&lt;/a&gt;. "There are millions of people in this country who have abused our visa system and circumvented our legal immigration process. It is a slap in the face to the working-class Ohioans whose wages are suffering."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Opponents counter that the policy would limit U.S. visits primarily to the rich.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"The fact that people would get their money back at departure doesn't address the issue that most people around the world don't have access to big sums of cash or to substantial credit," &lt;a href="https://www.msnbc.com/opinion/msnbc-opinion/jd-vance-immigration-visa-overstay-rcna96973"&gt;columnist Zeeshan Aleem wrote for MSNBC&lt;/a&gt;. "The U.S. would become an impossible travel destination for many and an undesirable travel destination for others."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Vance's bill has &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/s2656/details"&gt;not yet attracted any cosponsors&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h4&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/s3516"&gt;WIRED (Withholding Illegal Revenue Entering Drug Markets) Act&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt; &lt;p&gt;When an immigrant -- whether documented or undocumented -- sends money to their families or friends back in their home country, that's called a "remittance."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Republicans are concerned that some remittances help fund gang activity, violence, and cartels, particularly in nations like Mexico. In 2022, U.S. remittances comprised &lt;a href="https://www.dallasfed.org/research/swe/2023/swe2310"&gt;4.5% of Mexico's economy&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://oklahoma.gov/content/dam/ok/en/tax/documents/resources/rules-and-policies/agency-rules/Chapter95-2022.pdf#page=29"&gt;Since 2010&lt;/a&gt;, Oklahoma has been the &lt;a href="https://americafirstpolicy.com/issues/state-legislative-priority-international-wire-transfer-fees2"&gt;only&lt;/a&gt;  &lt;a href="https://cis.org/North/Heres-Research-Idea-Support-State-Taxes-Remittances"&gt;state&lt;/a&gt; to impose a fee on such transactions, set at 1%. Vance's bill would set a considerably larger federal 10% fee on international remittances.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"We cannot stand idly by as illegal immigrants and drug cartels profit from breaking our nation's laws," &lt;a href="https://www.vance.senate.gov/press-releases/senator-vance-rep-hern-introduce-bill-to-tax-international-money-transfers-by-cartels-and-illegal-immigrants/"&gt;Sen. Vance said in a press release&lt;/a&gt;. "This legislation is a commonsense solution to disincentivize illegal immigration and reduce the cartels' financial power."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Opponents counter that the bill would primarily hurt innocent low-income people who want to help their family back home.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Probably 99 percent of the people that send money back to Mexico and other countries, they send it back to feed their families," David Castillo, executive director of the Greater Oklahoma City Hispanic Chamber of Commerce, &lt;a href="https://journalrecord.com/2009/07/officials-defend-wire-transfer-fee-for-funding-drugenforcement-activities/"&gt;told Oklahoma's Journal Record in 2009 when the state law was enacted&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Vance's bill has &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/s3516/details"&gt;not yet attracted any cosponsors&lt;/a&gt;. The House version has also &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr6817/details"&gt;not yet attracted any cosponsors&lt;/a&gt; and hasn't received a vote in any of its five committees either.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h4&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/s2962"&gt;Drive American Act&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt; &lt;p&gt;As the climate crisis intensifies, congressional Democrats in 2021-22 enacted federal tax credits for customers who buy zero-emission or "plug-in" electric vehicles, &lt;a href="https://afdc.energy.gov/laws/409#:%7E:text=See%20the%20IRS%20Plug%2DIn,or%20placed%2Din%2Dservice."&gt;worth up to $7,500 per vehicle&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Republicans criticized the Biden administration's Energy Department for &lt;a href="https://www.politico.com/news/2024/05/03/biden-ev-tax-credit-rules-automakers-china-00155917"&gt;granting a reprieve on some of the law's ostensible "buy American" provisions&lt;/a&gt;. The Energy Department justified the move by noting that current production resources make it almost impossible to build such vehicles without Chinese minerals, at least for now.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Vance's bill would repeal all federal electric vehicle subsidies or tax credits, replacing them with a new tax credit providing an identical maximum amount -- up to $7,500 -- for a vehicle using gas or diesel fuel and built entirely in the U.S., if such a vehicle exists.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Right now, the official policy of the Biden administration is to spend billions of dollars on subsidies for electric vehicles made overseas," &lt;a href="https://www.vance.senate.gov/press-releases/senator-vance-unveils-legislation-to-eliminate-biden-ev-credits-promote-domestic-auto-manufacturing/"&gt;Sen. Vance said in a press release&lt;/a&gt;. "If we're subsidizing anything, it ought to be Ohio workers -- not the green energy daydreams that are offshoring their jobs to China."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Opponents counter that the current tax credits help both the environment and the domestic economy.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Making the switch to electric vehicles saves consumers money, improves our air quality, and advances our climate goals," &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/members/thomas_carper/300019"&gt;Sen. Tom Carper (D-DE)&lt;/a&gt;, Chair of the Senate Environment and Public Works Committee, &lt;a href="https://www.epw.senate.gov/public/index.cfm/2023/3/carper-statement-on-treasury-ev-tax-credit-guidance"&gt;said in a press release&lt;/a&gt;. "[Tax credits] will also encourage greater investment from American companies to make these vehicles here at home â critical to ensuring that the United States leads the world into the clean energy future."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Vance's bill has &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/s2962/details"&gt;not yet attracted any cosponsors&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h4&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/s3396"&gt;College Admissions Accountability Act&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt; &lt;p&gt;In June 2023, the Supreme Court struck down college affirmative action policies, which give preferential treatment to some applicants based on their race, in the decision &lt;a href="https://www.supremecourt.gov/opinions/22pdf/20-1199_hgdj.pdf"&gt;Students for Fair Admissions v. Harvard&lt;/a&gt;. The ruling was 6-2, with the conservative justices in favor.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Vance's bill would create a new "Office of the Special Inspector General for Unlawful Discrimination in Higher Education," housed within the Department of Education.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"For decades, America's higher education cartel has discriminated against applicants and students by adhering to racial preferences under the banner of 'equity,'" &lt;a href="https://www.vance.senate.gov/press-releases/senator-vance-introduces-legislation-to-crack-down-on-unlawful-discrimination-in-higher-education/"&gt;Sen. Vance said in a press release&lt;/a&gt;. "The Supreme Court's landmark decision... rightly called for an end to these unjust practices. This bill creates the means necessary to enforce the Court's decision."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Opponents counter that the Supreme Court decision was wrongly decided in the first place.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"The Court cements a superficial rule of colorblindness as a constitutional principle in an endemically segregated society where race has always mattered and continues to matter," &lt;a href="https://www.supremecourt.gov/opinions/22pdf/20-1199_hgdj.pdf#page=141"&gt;Justice Sonia Sotomayor wrote in dissent&lt;/a&gt;. "The Court subverts the constitutional guarantee of equal protection by further entrenching racial inequality in education, the very foundation of our democratic government and pluralistic society."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Vance's bill has attracted &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/s3396/cosponsors"&gt;five Republican cosponsors&lt;/a&gt;. The &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr6615"&gt;House version&lt;/a&gt; introduced by &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/members/jim_banks/412702"&gt;Rep. Jim Banks (R-IN3)&lt;/a&gt; has attracted &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr6615/cosponsors"&gt;three Republican cosponsors&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;      &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;  &lt;hr&gt;  &lt;p&gt;    Let us know what you think about these updates    by tooting us on &lt;a rel="me" href="https://mastodon.social/@GovTrack" title="Mastodon"&gt;&lt;i class="fab fa-mastodon"&gt;&lt;/i&gt; Mastodon&lt;/a&gt;    or &lt;a href="https://govtrack.us/contact" style="text-decoration: none"&gt;&lt;i class="fas fa-envelope"&gt;&lt;/i&gt; sending us an email&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;    			&lt;/div&gt;</description>
