    <item>
      <title>Yes, Congress did do some legislatin' this week - GovTrack.us</title>
      <link>https://govtrack.us/posts/430/2024-07-12_yes-congress-did-do-some-legislatin-this-week</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://govtrack.us/posts/430/2024-07-12_yes-congress-did-do-some-legislatin-this-week</guid>
      <description>&lt;div id="content"&gt; 				 			   	  				 &lt;h1&gt;Yes, Congress did do some legislatin&amp;#39; this week&lt;/h1&gt;  &lt;div class="row"&gt;     &lt;div class="col-md order-md-2" style="margin-bottom: 2em"&gt;         &lt;div class="ms-md-3" style="border: 1px solid #777; border-radius: 1em; padding: 1em; background-color: #F9F9F9;"&gt;         &lt;h2&gt;Get Legislative Recap Updates In Your Inbox!&lt;/h2&gt;         &lt;p&gt;Sign up (it&amp;rsquo;s free!) to get posts like this straight to your inbox. You&amp;rsquo;ll be able to choose posts from these categories:&lt;/p&gt;         &lt;p&gt;Legislative Preview &amp;nbsp; &amp;ndash; &amp;nbsp; Legislative Recap &amp;nbsp; &amp;ndash; &amp;nbsp; Analysis and Commentary &amp;nbsp; &amp;ndash; &amp;nbsp; News About GovTrack &amp;nbsp; &amp;ndash; &amp;nbsp; Using GovTrack Tips&lt;/p&gt;         &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://govtrack.us/accounts/lists" class="btn btn-primary"&gt;Sign Up &amp;raquo;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;      &lt;div class="col-md"&gt;        &lt;p&gt;           Jul 12, 2024           &amp;middot; by Amy West       &lt;/p&gt;        &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Update/Correction 7/13/2024: we mis-stated slightly the situation in North Dakota. We've revised that paragraph to indicate that the REAL ID process confirms citizenship for those who have it at the point of getting a state ID, but does not preclude a non-citizen from attempting to vote anyway. Despite this, there are no recorded instances in the Heritage database of that happening in ND.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;hr&gt; &lt;p&gt;You'd never know it from the news coverage this week, but Congress actually did some legislating this week.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Environmental Protection / Management&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr897"&gt;H.R. 897: Alabama Underwater Forest National Marine Sanctuary and Protection Act&lt;/a&gt; passed &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/votes/118-2024/h336"&gt;349-19&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr5441"&gt;H.R. 5441: Long Island Sound Restoration and Stewardship Reauthorization Act of 2023&lt;/a&gt; passed by &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/votes/118-2024/h337"&gt;333-51&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Messaging on Major Appliances&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr7637"&gt;H.R. 7637: Refrigerator Freedom Act&lt;/a&gt; passed &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/votes/118-2024/h341"&gt;212-192&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr7700"&gt;H.R. 7700: Stop Unaffordable Dishwasher Standards Act&lt;/a&gt; passed by &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/votes/118-2024/h343"&gt;214-192&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;Both bills say they will prevent energy efficiency standards that are too costly or technologically infeasible even though there is no indication that any such regulations exist or are planned.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Election "Security"&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr8281/summary"&gt;H.R. 8281: Safeguard American Voter Eligibility Act&lt;/a&gt; passed by &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/votes/118-2024/h345"&gt;221-198&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;This bill would do two primary things: first, it would require proof of citizenship when registering to vote and second, it would make it easier for private citizens to sue election officials.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;It's already law that a voter must be a citizen and 18 and over to vote. What kind of proof the prospective voter must provide when registering varies by state. North Dakota does not do voter registration at all. But, in general, because of the REAL ID system for getting driving licenses now in use nationwide, in &lt;a href="https://www.usvotefoundation.org/am-i-registered-to-vote-backgrounder"&gt;states where you can simultaneously register to vote&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://www.dhs.gov/real-id/real-id-faqs"&gt;license applicants already &lt;em&gt;do&lt;/em&gt; provide proof of citizenship&lt;/a&gt; in the form of birth certificates, passports, proof of naturalization, etc in order to get a license. Is it possible that someone might get registered inappropriately? Yes. But as we'll note below, it's incredibly rare.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Both the Heritage Foundation (conservative; the folks behind &lt;a href="https://www.project2025.org/"&gt;Project 2025&lt;/a&gt;) and the Brennan Center for Justice (liberal) have studied non-citizen voting. &lt;a href="https://www.heritage.org/voterfraud/search?combine=citizenship&amp;amp;state=All&amp;amp;year=&amp;amp;case_type=All&amp;amp;fraud_type=All&amp;amp;page=0"&gt;Heritage&lt;/a&gt; found 24 instances between 2003-2023 and &lt;a href="https://www.brennancenter.org/our-work/research-reports/noncitizen-voting-missing-millions"&gt;Brennan&lt;/a&gt; found 30 incidents across 42 jurisdictions and 23.5 million votes cast in 2016. As the Bipartisan Policy Center notes, &lt;a href="https://bipartisanpolicy.org/blog/four-things-to-know-about-noncitizen-voting/"&gt;this is simply not a significant problem with the U. S. election system&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This bill will not become law this Congress, but it could come back next year and potentially succeed depending on the outcome of the election.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Also: North Dakota &lt;a href="https://www.dot.nd.gov/driver/real-id-information"&gt;requires proof of citizenship or residency to get a state ID&lt;/a&gt; which is one of the things voters must present at the polls. So even in a state without voter registration, citizenship for voters that have it is still confirmed before voting. It's possible someone could just try to vote anyway as a non-citizen, but the &lt;a href="https://www.heritage.org/voterfraud/search?state=ND"&gt;Heritage database&lt;/a&gt; shows a total of three records from 1982-present and none for a non-citizen attempting to vote.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Appropriations&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr8772"&gt;H.R. 8772: Legislative Branch Appropriations Act, 2025&lt;/a&gt; failed by &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/votes/118-2024/h352"&gt;205-213&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;It's not entirely clear why the 10 Republicans who voted against it did so since this would be the most conservative version of the appropriations they'd see. &lt;a href="https://www.washingtonexaminer.com/news/house/3078148/house-gop-fails-pass-bill-funding-legislative-branch/"&gt;Rep. Rosendale though said it wasn't enough&lt;/a&gt; to the Washington Examiner.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Congressional Disapproval of Nondiscrimination&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hjres165"&gt;H.J.Res. 165: Providing for congressional disapproval under chapter 8 of title 5, United States Code, of the rule submitted by the Department of Education relating to âNondiscrimination on the Basis of Sex in Education Programs or Activities Receiving Federal Financial Assistanceâ&lt;/a&gt; passed &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/votes/118-2024/h354"&gt;210-205&lt;/a&gt; on a party line vote.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Veto Override (failed like almost all override attempts)&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hjres109"&gt;H.J.Res. 109: Providing for congressional disapproval under chapter 8 of title 5, United States Code, of the rule submitted by the Securities and Exchange Commission relating to âStaff Accounting Bulletin No. 121â&lt;/a&gt; failed &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/votes/118-2024/h355"&gt;228-184&lt;/a&gt; because veto overrides require a 2/3rd majority to pass.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;The regulation at issue is very complicated and relates to transparency of crypto holdings by financial entites, but &lt;a href="https://crsreports.congress.gov/product/pdf/IN/IN12358"&gt;the Congressional Research Service is here to explain&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Inherent Contempt&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hres1344"&gt;H.Res. 1344: Finding that Merrick Garland, Attorney General of the United States, is in contempt of the House of Representatives for disobeying a certain subpoena&lt;/a&gt; failed &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/votes/118-2024/h353"&gt;204-210&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;Four Republicans did vote against it, but more consequential were the 12 who didn't cast a vote at all. It may come back for another round of voting.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Scheduling note&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;p&gt;Next week is the Republican Nominating Convention and both chambers are out all week. We'll do another mailbag on Wednesday, so if there's something you'd really like us to cover in it, let us know.&lt;/p&gt;      &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;  &lt;hr&gt;  &lt;p&gt;    Let us know what you think about these updates    by tooting us on &lt;a rel="me" href="https://mastodon.social/@GovTrack" title="Mastodon"&gt;&lt;i class="fab fa-mastodon"&gt;&lt;/i&gt; Mastodon&lt;/a&gt;    or &lt;a href="https://govtrack.us/contact" style="text-decoration: none"&gt;&lt;i class="fas fa-envelope"&gt;&lt;/i&gt; sending us an email&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;    			&lt;/div&gt;</description>
